Linux has completed its 20 years of existence.
In these 20 years it has seen phenomenal growth and support from industry as well as individuals.
Today linux runs in more embedded systems than any other OS.
The smart phone market is dominated by android which is also a linux derivative.
Linux runs in the servers that powers facebook,twitter,amazon and other high data and security servers.
With the world slowly waking up to the open source initiatives and computing moving towards cloud, the competitors
of linux are having a hard time.
The future of linux looks bright from where we look today and gives us the hope that the penguin will keep smiling.
